  <div class="sec2_content">
    <h2 data-i18n="about.p1">
      Since 2018 I work at the intersection of IT, product and digital —
      plugging into businesses at active growth, when digital infrastructure is
      needed but processes and team aren't yet in place.
    </h2>
    <h2 data-i18n="about.p2">
      Off-hours: economic strategy games, gardening, game design at
      Syrnik.dev. Same muscle — systems that compound slowly.
    </h2>
    <div class="sec2_paragraph">
      <p class="left" data-i18n="about.blend">
        Art direction meets digital operations
      </p>
      <div class="right">
        <p data-i18n="about.desc1">
          My core role — walk into unstructured processes of growing businesses
          and turn them into working systems. Fix product and technical logic,
          set up baseline architecture, put order between business, design, and
          engineering. 300+ projects since 2018, personally or under my
          management.
        </p>
        <p data-i18n="about.desc2">
          The job isn't to do everything by hand. It's to leave behind a stable
          platform — a clear product, a baseline technical structure, and the
          operational order a full IT team can later stand on. One person,
          before the org chart exists.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
